  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for openvswitch",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for openvswitch fixes the following issues:\n\t  \n- openvswitch was updated to 2.5.11 \n- CVE-2020-27827: Fixed a memory leak when parsing lldp packets (bsc#1181345)\t  \n- datapath: Clear the L4 portion of the key for 'later' fragments\n- datapath: Properly set L4 keys on 'later' IP fragments\n- ofproto-dpif: Fix using uninitialised memory in user_action_cookie.\n- stream-ssl: Fix crash on NULL private key and valid certificate.\n- datapath: fix flow actions reallocation\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
